%%[doesWhat doclatex
A Handle represents a file.
The implementation is here is a stripped down version from the one in GHC.IOBase,
see there for documentation, with the following differences to be kept in mind:
\begin{itemize}
\item No concurrency is offered in UHC.
\item Use of MVar's is left but is only there to minimize the differences with GHC.
\item DuplexHandle for read/write streams is left in the code, but is (as of 20090416) not offered.
\end{itemize}

As of 20090412:
A Handle is defined in Prelude as well, hidden here, to be sorted out when the implementation here
is functioning well.
